  "text": "From our present results, it was clear that the parental NCTC 2071A cells successfully attached to and spread on absorbed fibronectin, but failed to organize fibronectin into an extensive fibrillar network. The most likely explanation is that the cell attachment receptor is functional in these cells but the matrix assembly receptor is missing and its function can be restored either by adding exogenous gangliosides (36, [CITATION_1] or altering the expression of complex cell surface gangliosides by a yet unknown mechanism.",
